              "free_text": [
                " The experiment was performed at ISAC I",
                "facility at TRIUMF in Vancouver using the TUDA",
                " (TRIUMF-U.K. Detector Array) chamber"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was 25mu-g/cm2 7LiF on a 10 mu-g/cm2",
                "carbon backing. Elastic scattering on F nuclei was",
                "used for calibration of detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " TUDA chamber contained Louvain-Edinburgh",
                "Detector Array (LEDA), which consists of eight",
                "separate azimuthal sectors, each with 16 radial",
                "elements. This annular detector is 300 mu-m thick and",
                "its active area spans radii from 50mm to 129.9mm. LEDA",
                "was placed at a distance of 7.2 cm form the target"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The S2 is a double sided silicon strip",
                "detector consisting of a single element that is",
                "divided into 16 azimuthal sectors on the back side",
                "and 48 rings on the front. This 500 mu-m thick",
                "detector has inner radius of 11.5 mm and an outer",
                "radius of 35 mm. S2 detector was placed at the",
                "distance of 13 cm from the target"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between LEDA and S2 detectors was",
                "required to identify the selected events."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Radioactive 8Li(2+) beam at an energy of 11 MeV with an",
                "intensity of (9 - 16)*E+6/s was produced using ISAC 1",
                "facility. Protons with energy of 500 MeV and current",
                "up to 100 mu-A were steered onto production targets to",
                "produce 8Li nuclei which are separated by mass",
                "separator and accelerated."
              ]
            }
          ],
